---
title: Turkish-Spiced Chicken in Apricot Sauce with Lemon Almond Rice & Harissa-Roasted Asparagus
description: Sure, you could have plain chicken for dinner—but why not dig into this warmly spiced version that’s smothered in tangy apricot pan sauce instead? Here, we season the chicken with a Turkish spice blend of cumin, garlic, coriander, allspice, and chili flakes, then serve it with a jammy, buttery apricot sauce and pair it all with sweet-smoky-tangy harissa-roasted carrots and almond-studded rice.
